datafield.subfield: A Study of Multiple Jet Production at Transverse Energy Near 20-GeV
A study of multiple jet production at transverse energy near 20-GeV
International Europhysics Conference on High Energy Physics, Budapest, Hungary, July 12-18,2001

We present data on multiple jet production for transverse energies greater than 20 GeV in $p\overline{p}$ collisions at $\sqrt{s}$ = 1.8 TeV. QCD calculations in the parton shower approximation (PYTHIA) and in the next-to-leading order approximation (JETRAD) show discrepancies with data for three and four-jet production. This disagreement is especially apparent in multiple jet angular and transverse momentum distributions.
